MetalLB LoadBalancer with NGINX on Bare-Metal Kubernetes
1️⃣ Prerequisites

A working Kubernetes cluster (multi-node or single-node).

kubectl installed and configured.

All nodes on the same network/subnet.

Container runtime installed (e.g., containerd).

Verify all nodes are ready:

kubectl get nodes -o wide

Expected output should show all nodes in Ready state with internal IPs.

2️⃣ Install MetalLB

Apply the MetalLB manifests:

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/metallb/metallb/v0.15.3/config/manifests/metallb-native.yaml

Verify pods:

kubectl get pods -n metallb-system -o wide

Expected output:

controller running

speaker running on all nodes

⚠️ If some speaker pods are in ContainerCreating or CrashLoopBackOff, ensure all nodes can communicate on the network.

3️⃣ Configure MetalLB IP Pool

Create metallb-config.yaml:

apiVersion: metallb.io/v1beta1
kind: IPAddressPool
metadata:
  name: default-address-pool
  namespace: metallb-system
spec:
  addresses:
  - 192.168.31.240-192.168.31.250
---
apiVersion: metallb.io/v1beta1
kind: L2Advertisement
metadata:
  name: default-l2
  namespace: metallb-system
spec:
  ipAddressPools:
  - default-address-pool

Apply the configuration:

kubectl apply -f metallb-config.yaml

Verify:

kubectl get ipaddresspool -n metallb-system
kubectl get l2advertisement -n metallb-system
4️⃣ Configure /etc/hosts

Add entries for testing (on all nodes where you’ll run curl):

127.0.0.1 localhost
127.0.1.1 vga

192.168.31.241 test1.local
192.168.31.242 test2.local

These IPs correspond to the MetalLB-assigned LoadBalancer IP for your NGINX Ingress.

5️⃣ NGINX Service 1

Create test-nginx-fixed-all.yaml:

apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: test-nginx-index
data:
  index.html: |
    <html>
    <head><title>Test NGINX Ingress</title></head>
    <body>
      <h1>Success! NGINX Ingress is working.</h1>
    </body>
    </html>
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: test-nginx
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: test-nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: test-nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.25
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        volumeMounts:
        - mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html
          name: nginx-index
      volumes:
      - name: nginx-index
        configMap:
          name: test-nginx-index
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: test-nginx
spec:
  selector:
    app: test-nginx
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80

Apply and restart deployment:

kubectl apply -f test-nginx-fixed-all.yaml
kubectl rollout restart deployment test-nginx
6️⃣ NGINX Ingress 1

Create test-ingress.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: test-ingress
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: test1.local
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: test-nginx
            port:
              number: 80

Apply:

kubectl apply -f test-ingress.yaml

Test:

curl http://test1.local

Expected output:

<h1>Success! NGINX Ingress is working.</h1>
7️⃣ NGINX Service 2

Create test-nginx2.yaml:

apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: test-nginx2-index
data:
  index.html: |
    <html>
    <head><title>Test NGINX Ingress 2</title></head>
    <body>
      <h1>Success! This is NGINX Service 2.</h1>
    </body>
    </html>
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: test-nginx2
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: test-nginx2
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: test-nginx2
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.25
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        volumeMounts:
        - mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html
          name: nginx2-index
      volumes:
      - name: nginx2-index
        configMap:
          name: test-nginx2-index
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: test-nginx2
spec:
  selector:
    app: test-nginx2
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80

Apply and restart deployment:

kubectl apply -f test-nginx2.yaml
kubectl rollout restart deployment test-nginx2
8️⃣ Multi-Host Ingress

Create multi-host-ingress.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: multi-host-ingress
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: test1.local
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: test-nginx
            port:
              number: 80
  - host: test2.local
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: test-nginx2
            port:
              number: 80

Apply:

kubectl apply -f multi-host-ingress.yaml

Test both hosts:

curl http://test1.local
curl http://test2.local

Expected output:

test1.local → NGINX Service 1 page

test2.local → NGINX Service 2 page

9️⃣ Verification Commands

Check pods:

kubectl get pods -l app=test-nginx
kubectl get pods -l app=test-nginx2

Check services:

kubectl get svc

Check ingress:

kubectl get ingress multi-host-ingress -o wide

Check endpoints:

kubectl get endpoints test-nginx
kubectl get endpoints test-nginx2
🔹 Notes

Ensure MetalLB IP matches /etc/hosts.

If NGINX shows default “Welcome to nginx” page, check ConfigMap mount and volume paths.

Always do rollout restart after ConfigMap changes:

kubectl rollout restart deployment <deployment-name>

Two Ingress resources cannot share the same host/path, use one Ingress for multiple hosts as done in multi-host-ingress.yaml.

Diagram (Conceptual)
test1.local → Ingress → test-nginx → Pods (Node1, Node2, Node3)
test2.local → Ingress → test-nginx2 → Pods (Node1, Node2)
MetalLB IP: 192.168.31.241 → Routes traffic to Ingress

This version is ready for sharing or using as a reference to deploy MetalLB + NGINX Ingress with multiple hosts.
